            and mayest thou, evening star, quickly come, and bring 

            again her secretly, 1 whom thou art taking away.1

Timaria's kiss, like bird-lime, clings 

            About the happy lips she blesses ; 

            Her eye its sun-like radiance flings 

            Beneath her dark overshadowing tresses. 

            One look, fond lover, and you're burnt ; 

            One torch, and all your strength is nought; 

            And Love himself this lesson learnt, 

            Late in her nets a captive caught. J. H. M.

